433
00:19:45,293 --> 00:19:46,193
even how we act out.

434
00:19:47,312 --> 00:19:50,816
So basically, rather than write things that happen to the queen, the real story is in

435
00:19:50,816 --> 00:19:52,337
how she can respond.

436
00:19:52,337 --> 00:19:57,041
Generally, we give yes or no choices because those are most functional from a design standpoint.

437
00:19:57,041 --> 00:19:59,243
Players tend to sometimes swipe without reading.

438
00:19:59,243 --> 00:20:01,065
They've known one way is yes and one way is no.

439
00:20:01,065 --> 00:20:05,469
But we went for tonal variety where possible, just because sometimes it's so much fun to

440
00:20:05,469 --> 00:20:06,770
emphatically say nope.

441
00:20:07,212 --> 00:20:09,434
instead of no to some incompetent guy.

442
00:20:09,434 --> 00:20:12,195
And all the guys in Reigns for Majesty are incompetent.

443
00:20:12,195 --> 00:20:13,796
Like, every character is ridiculous,

444
00:20:13,796 --> 00:20:15,738
but the dudes are especially so.

445
00:20:15,738 --> 00:20:19,140
And I gave them all, like, really ridiculous names,

446
00:20:19,140 --> 00:20:21,101
because fuck it.

447
00:20:21,101 --> 00:20:22,182
Thank you.

448
00:20:22,182 --> 00:20:24,403
I also tried wherever possible to make sure

449
00:20:24,403 --> 00:20:26,945
that the binary choices were more nuanced

450
00:20:26,945 --> 00:20:30,407
than accept this or reject it, or be nice or be mean.

451
00:20:30,407 --> 00:20:33,029
I hope that Reigns 2 would also invite players

